{
  "stem": "9262.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I asked them, this happened in 1939, as far as I can remember.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They said, oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I said, well, how did you manage to get out and come to England?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they came to England before the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they told me that they were told by the Jewish organization in Poland, through the Jewish organization that was left in Germany-- because only Polish Jews were deported, but German Jews were still living in Germany.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that the papers have arrived for them to go to England.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All they had to do come back to Germany and get that paper permit in order to go to England via Holland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So some of these people, who were children at the time, went to Germany, obtained the relative documents-- the permits-- to leave Germany, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] went to Holland-- from Germany to Holland-- and from Holland to England.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That's how they reached England before the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But this was not something that you were aware of at the time?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wasn't aware at all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had no inkling.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was all known to me afterwards, when I was already in England.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had no knowledge whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we were deported as a family unit, and we stayed together as a family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we had no idea, whatsoever, that this was happening.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now the people who were living in this factory had some contacts with the Zionist organization in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from Germany, they got in touch with the Zionist organization in Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my brother, who was in the Habonim movement, got to know [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that arrangements were made for him to leave for Israel, which was Palestine at the time.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
